name: After Kurt Hermann Eduard Karl Julius Schwitters
description:
Tribute one of the leaders of 20th century art, Kurt Schwitters (1887-1948) was a German artist who was born in Hanover, Germany. Schwitters worked in several genres and media, including dadaism, constructivism, surrealism, poetry, sound, painting, sculpture, graphic design, typography, and what came to be known as installation art.


00:10 seconds, 500x624 dimensions, stereo video collage with ambient instrumental audio.
